com.bluegosling.collections

Interface OrderedQueue<E>

  • Type Parameters:
    E - the type of element stored in the queue
    All Superinterfaces:
    Collection<E>, Iterable<E>, Queue<E>
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    MeldableOrderedQueue<E,Q>, PriorityQueues.MeldableQueue<E>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    BinomialHeapQueue, ConcurrentSkipListOrderedQueue, FibonacciHeapOrderedQueue, LockFreeSkipListBlockingQueue, SetBackedOrderedQueue, SkewHeapOrderedQueue

    public interface OrderedQueue<E>
extends Queue<E>
    A queue that retrieves items in priority order instead of in LIFO order. This sort of queue is generally backed by a heap.

    The Java Collections Framework includes such a queue, PriorityQueue, that is backed by a binary heap. Although that class does not actually implement this interface, it could since it contains all of the necessary methods. This interface exists to provide a contract for other implementations of ordered queues.

    Note that this interface is a simple extension of the standard Queue interface. This package also includes a separate PriorityQueue interface, that provides an alternate contract with additional operations, that is incompatible with that standard interface.

    See Also:
    PriorityQueue, PriorityQueue

    • Method Detail

      • comparator

        Comparator<? super E> comparator()
        The comparator used to compare elements and determine their order. If two elements are equal according to the comparator, the order of when the elements will be retrieved from the queue is undefined.

        For queues that order elements according to their natural ordering, this method will return null.

        Returns:
        the comparator used to compare elements or null if elements are compared according to their natural ordering

      • fromJrePriorityQueue

        Adapts the JRE's PriorityQueue to this interface.
        Parameters:
        queue - a priority queue
        Returns:
        a view of the given priority queue as an OrderedQueue
